'''Baenan''' (''Baenã, Baenán, Baena'') is a poorly attested language of [[Brazil]]. The last remaining speaker lived in [[Bahia]], [[Brazil]] in 1940. The language of this speaker was associated with the Baenan language as the last members of the Baenan tribe lived in Paragaçú, [[Bahia]], near where the language was attested. There are nine known words of Baenan:<ref>{{cite journal | last = Loukotka | first =Čestmír | authorlink = Čestmír Loukotka | title = Documents et Vocabulaires Inédits de Langues et de Dialects Sud-Américains | journal = [[Journal de la Société des Américanistes]] | volume = 52 | pages = 7–60 | doi = 10.3406/jsa.1963.2001 | year = 1963}}</ref>
#''eželẽ'' - deer #''bakurí'' - venison #''kelemés'' - fire #''patarak'' - jaguar #''kadašužé'' - black person #''bonikro'' - pig #''pititiɲga'' - rat #''pitirát'' - monkey #''šẽšẽ'' - bull
