{{Infobox company | name = Chippewa Boots | logo = | type = [[Subsidiary]] | foundation = {{Start date and age|1901}} in [[Chippewa Falls, Wisconsin]], [[United States]] | founder = | location = | location_city = [[Chippewa Falls, Wisconsin]] | location_country = [[United States]] | area_served = | key_people = | industry = [[Footwear]] and [[Raincoat|rainwear]] | products = [[Boot]]s | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = [[Justin Brands]] | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.chippewaboots.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
[[File:Chippewa Falls 2006 A.jpg|thumb|The Chippewa Shoe Manufacturing Company, now in the National Register of Historic Places.]] '''Chippewa Boots''', originally known as Chippewa Shoe Manufacturing Company, is a manufacturer of [[footwear]], principally men's work and recreational [[boots]]. It also manufactures a limited line of heavy and casual shoes, and some women's footwear. It was founded in [[Chippewa Falls, Wisconsin]], in 1901.<ref>[https://www.chippewaboots.com/heritage/ Heritage: A Retrospect of the Chippewa Story - Chippewa Boots U.S.A.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214115323/https://www.chippewaboots.com/heritage/ |date=2013-12-14 }}. ChippewaBoots.com. Retrieved on Dec 10, 2013.</ref> In 1984 it was acquired by [[Justin Brands]], which was in turn acquired by [[Berkshire Hathaway]] in August 2000.<ref>[https://www.justinboots.com/en/heritage.html Justin Boots Heritage] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213172407/http://www.justinboots.com/en/heritage.html |date=2013-12-13 }}. JustinBoots.com. Retrieved on Dec 10, 2013.</ref> Other companies under Justin Brands include [[Justin Boots]], Justin Original Workboots, [[Nocona Boots]], and [[Tony Lama Boots]].
